<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<!-- Chapter 1: Introduction to Robotics -->
<chapter xml:id="ch_intro_robotics" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">

  <title>Introduction to Robotics</title>

  <!-- Chapter Introduction -->
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Welcome to the world of robotics! This chapter introduces the fundamental concepts 
      that form the foundation of modern robotics systems. We'll explore what makes a 
      robot a robot, how different subsystems work together, and the basic principles 
      of robot control.
    </p>
    <p>
      By the end of this chapter, you will understand:
      <ul>
        <li>The key components that make up a robotic system</li>
        <li>How robots perceive, plan, and control their actions</li>
        <li>The difference between open-loop and closed-loop control</li>
        <li>The fundamentals of PID control for precise robot movements</li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <!-- Include sections -->
  <xi:include href="./sec_what_is_robotics.ptx" />
  <xi:include href="./sec_robot_subsystems.ptx" />
  <xi:include href="./sec_perception_planning_control.ptx" />
  <xi:include href="./sec_control_fundamentals.ptx" />
  <xi:include href="./sec_pid_concepts.ptx" />

  <!-- Exercises -->
  <xi:include href="./ex_intro_robotics.ptx"/>

  <!-- Chapter Conclusion -->
  <conclusion>
    <p>
      In this chapter, we've covered the essential building blocks of robotic systems. 
      You've learned about robot subsystems, the perception-planning-control loop, and 
      fundamental control concepts including PID control. These concepts will be the 
      foundation for everything we explore in this course.
    </p>
    <p>
      In the next chapters, we'll dive deeper into each of these areas, exploring 
      advanced sensing techniques, intelligent planning algorithms, and sophisticated 
      control methods that enable robots to operate in complex, real-world environments.
    </p>
  </conclusion>

</chapter>
